    {
      "Text": "An update for python-pip is now available for openEuler-20.03-LTS-SP1 and openEuler-20.03-LTS-SP2.",
      "Title": "Summary",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "pip is the package installer for Python. You can use pip to install packages from the Python Package Index and other indexes.\n\nSecurity Fix(es):\n\nA flaw was found in python-pip in the way it handled Unicode separators in git references. A remote attacker could possibly use this issue to install a different revision on a repository. The highest threat from this vulnerability is to data integrity.(CVE-2021-3572)",
      "Title": "Description",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "An update for python-pip is now available for openEuler-20.03-LTS-SP1 and openEuler-20.03-LTS-SP2.\n\nopenEuler Security has rated this update as having a security impact of medium. A Common Vunlnerability Scoring System(CVSS)base score,which gives a detailed severity rating, is available for each vulnerability from the CVElink(s) in the References section.",
      "Title": "Topic",
      "Type": "General"
    },
